1
00:00:17,360 --> 00:00:19,680
Peter and Benjamin hopped past the shop.

2
00:00:20,700 --> 00:00:25,680
Suddenly Peter stopped. "Look!" he said.

3
00:00:26,480 --> 00:00:29,140
"Candy! Let's get some!"

4
00:00:30,400 --> 00:00:33,080
"Do you have any money?" Benjamin asked.

5
00:00:34,060 --> 00:00:36,330
"No," Peter said. "Do you?"

6
00:00:36,380 --> 00:00:38,640
"No," Benjamin said.

7
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:45,420
The bunnies hopped away sadly.

8
00:00:47,160 --> 00:00:49,300
Then Peter saw something else.

9
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:52,280
"An old boot!" he cried.

10
00:00:53,720 --> 00:00:58,060
Benjamin looked at the boot. "It's a nice brown boot."

11
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:05,820
"Let's take it to the shopkeeper," Peter said. "Then he will give us candy."

12
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:16,100
The bunnies dragged the boot to the shop.

13
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:25,140
The shopkeeper frowned. "One boot? What can I do with one boot?"

14
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:28,200
"You can sell it," Peter said.

15
00:01:28,660 --> 00:01:31,220
"You can put things in it," Benjamin said.

16
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:43,900
The shopkeeper looked at the boot again. "Okay," he said. "I will take it."

17
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:47,320
The shopkeeper took the boot.

18
00:01:50,060 --> 00:01:52,100
Peter and Benjamin got some candy.

19
00:01:54,180 --> 00:01:55,860
The bunnies were happy now.

20
00:02:01,960 --> 00:02:04,680
As they hopped away, they saw a mouse.

21
00:02:05,460 --> 00:02:26,800
"My house is gone!" she cried. "It is an old brown boot."

22
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:42,140
Benjamin gulped. Peter dropped a few candies.

23
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:46,380
"You lost your boot!" he said.

24
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:53,820
"Yes!" the mouse cried. "What will I do?"

25
00:02:55,860 --> 00:02:58,880
Peter thought fast. "We'll look for your house."

26
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:06,040
The bunnies hopped back to the shop.

27
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:10,800
"We need the boot," Benjamin said.

28
00:03:11,740 --> 00:03:18,040
The shopkeeper shook his head. "Sorry," he said. "Mrs. Tiggy-Winkle just bought it."

29
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:21,460
"Oh no!" Peter said.

30
00:03:21,510 --> 00:03:25,720
"We must find Mrs. Tiggy-Winkle," Benjamin said.

31
00:03:28,660 --> 00:03:31,740
The bunnies hopped fast to Mrs. Tiggy-Winkle's house.

32
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:37,060
Candies fell out of their pockets, but they did not see them.

33
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:42,240
The bunnies knocked on Mrs. Tiggy-Winkle's door.

34
00:03:48,900 --> 00:03:51,260
"Do you have the boot?" Peter asked.

35
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:57,360
Mrs. Tiggy-Winkle sighed. "I painted a pretty picture on it."

36
00:03:58,060 --> 00:04:02,040
"I wanted to use it for dirty socks, but it was too heavy."

37
00:04:05,220 --> 00:04:07,640
Peter grinned. "Can we have it?"

38
00:04:09,160 --> 00:04:11,260
"No," Mrs. Tiggy-Winkle said.

39
00:04:12,260 --> 00:04:32,940
She held up an old hat. "Jemima gave me this hat. I gave her the boot."

40
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:40,420
The bunnies hopped to the farm.

41
00:04:45,540 --> 00:04:50,700
"Jemima!" Benjamin called. "We are looking for an old boot."

42
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:58,920
"Oh," Jemima said. "I wanted to make a nest in that boot, but it was too small for my eggs."

43
00:04:59,780 --> 00:05:02,940
"Great!" Peter said. "Can we have the boot?"

44
00:05:03,900 --> 00:05:12,260
"No," Jemima said. "I gave the boot to Tom Kitten. He gave me hay."

45
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,320
The bunnies hopped away.

46
00:05:26,740 --> 00:05:28,960
They found Tom near some big rocks.

47
00:05:30,140 --> 00:05:32,900
"Do you have the boot?" Benjamin called.

48
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:45,780
"Oh," Tom nodded sadly. "Yes."

49
00:05:45,830 --> 00:05:53,400
But he pointed to the boot. It was stuck between two rocks.

50
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:56,890
"We need that boot," Peter said.

51
00:05:56,940 --> 00:05:59,980
"Can we have it?" Benjamin asked.

52
00:06:02,660 --> 00:06:07,960
"Oh, okay," Tom said. "I will give you the boot."

53
00:06:08,010 --> 00:06:12,300
"Will you give me some candy?"

54
00:06:13,600 --> 00:06:18,760
"Okay." Peter reached into his pockets. He gasped.

55
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,220
"Where is all my candy?"

56
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:30,220
Peter had just one piece left. He gave it to Tom.

57
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:37,000
"Bye, Tom!" the bunnies said.

58
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:54,820
The bunnies grabbed the boot. They pulled hard, but it was still stuck.

59
00:07:11,340 --> 00:07:12,720
The bunnies were sad.

60
00:07:14,140 --> 00:07:15,740
All the candy was gone.

61
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:19,240
The mouse's boot was stuck.

62
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:24,080
"We must tell the mouse," Benjamin said.

63
00:07:24,580 --> 00:07:26,940
"She will be mad," Peter said.

64
00:07:29,060 --> 00:07:30,740
"Look! Here she comes."

65
00:07:32,660 --> 00:07:34,700
The mouse ran toward the bunnies.

66
00:07:37,340 --> 00:07:44,320
Suddenly she stopped. "My boot!" the mouse gasped.

67
00:07:47,940 --> 00:07:51,280
"Did someone paint a picture on my boot?"

68
00:07:52,860 --> 00:07:58,480
"Yes," Benjamin said. "Mrs. Tiggy-Winkle painted a picture on your boot."

69
00:08:03,220 --> 00:08:05,320
The mouse looked inside the boot.

70
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:10,220
"Did someone put feathers on my boot?"

71
00:08:11,620 --> 00:08:16,160
"Yes," Peter said. "Jemima put feathers on your boot."

72
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:19,820
The mouse looked at the rocks.

73
00:08:20,520 --> 00:08:23,240
"Did someone get my boot stuck?"

74
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:30,960
"Yes," Benjamin said sadly. "And we can't get it out."

75
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,720
The mouse laughed.

76
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:52,620
"Now my boot is pretty. My bed is soft. And nobody can take my boot."

77
00:08:53,940 --> 00:08:55,840
Peter and Benjamin laughed too.

78
00:08:59,780 --> 00:09:07,400
"Thank you for finding my house," the mouse said. "I found something for you too."

79
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:12,820
The mouse held out their candy.

